00:35:56.890 --> 00:35:59.110
On the right side we
have something that we

00:35:59.110 --> 00:36:01.570
call multiple rewarded ads.

00:36:01.570 --> 00:36:03.790
In this particular
example, not only

00:36:03.790 --> 00:36:07.090
are you offering the user
the choice to see an ad,

00:36:07.090 --> 00:36:10.390
you're actually offering them
a choice of which ad to see.

00:36:10.390 --> 00:36:12.790
And our data shows
that when you actually

00:36:12.790 --> 00:36:15.580
design the format in
this way, users actually

00:36:15.580 --> 00:36:19.460
end up picking an ad that
they have some investment in,

00:36:19.460 --> 00:36:21.490
they end up being more
engaged in the ad,

00:36:21.490 --> 00:36:24.340
and that results in
more conversions.

00:36:24.340 --> 00:36:26.410
These formats have been
designed specifically

00:36:26.410 --> 00:36:28.060
to make sure that
when you do try

00:36:28.060 --> 00:36:31.810
to monetize your non-spenders,
you do not end up sacrificing

00:36:31.810 --> 00:36:33.315
the in-game experience.

00:36:36.880 --> 00:36:39.640
Another important
piece of monetization

00:36:39.640 --> 00:36:43.330
is making sure that you're
optimizing every opportunity

00:36:43.330 --> 00:36:45.010
to own revenue.

00:36:45.010 --> 00:36:48.370
And normally this is met
using mediation and working

00:36:48.370 --> 00:36:51.550
with many different
network partners.

00:36:51.550 --> 00:36:54.760
Mediation is a crucial
strategy for our publishers

00:36:54.760 --> 00:36:57.280
to help them find
niche markets of demand

00:36:57.280 --> 00:36:59.470
across geo and format.

00:36:59.470 --> 00:37:02.560
In theory, mediation ensures
that you're getting the highest

00:37:02.560 --> 00:37:05.410
CPM for every impression
by making sure

00:37:05.410 --> 00:37:07.900
that the networks that have
historically offered the best

00:37:07.900 --> 00:37:10.810
performance get called
first, and then you

00:37:10.810 --> 00:37:12.820
proceed down a daisy chain.

00:37:12.820 --> 00:37:15.400
But what happens when a
lower-priority network

00:37:15.400 --> 00:37:20.340
is actually willing to pay more
for a particular impression?

00:37:20.340 --> 00:37:23.730
That's actually where we
believe we can come in and help.

00:37:23.730 --> 00:37:26.550
With the new product
that we just announced,

00:37:26.550 --> 00:37:29.040
which is called
Open Bidding, we now

00:37:29.040 --> 00:37:32.430
take the promise of
monetization to the next level.

00:37:32.430 --> 00:37:34.710
First, we make it
easier than ever

00:37:34.710 --> 00:37:37.170
